projects.name: Predicting Laptop Price Using Machine Learning Algorithms
projects.description: Developed and deployed a machine learning model for laptop price prediction by leveraging Python for algorithm implementation, Streamlit for intuitive front-end design, and Google Colab for both data visualization and model creation. Utilized historical laptop model data to accurately forecast prices, demonstrating proficiency in end-to-end ML development and visualization.

projects.name: Movie Recommendation System
projects.description: Implemented a movie recommendation system in Python using Word2Vec and cosine similarity. Processed descriptions, trained Word2Vec models, and calculated cosine similarity scores. Improved user experience with an efficient recommendation engine, delivering personalized suggestions by analyzing semantic relationships in movie descriptions.

projects.name: Smart Estate: Decentralized Real Estate Application using Blockchain
projects.description: Developed a smart real estate application using blockchain technologies such as solidity and hardhat along with reactjs as front end technology and mongoDB for backend. Using this web application one can buy and sell their property easily.

experiences.description: Facilitated administrative functions as the Secretary for the Graphics (GFX) division within the IT Council. Supported council operations, maintaining accurate records, organizing meetings, and managing communication channels.

Served as Secretary for the GFX/VFX division within the Entrepreneurship and Innovation Cell (E-Cell), overseeing administrative tasks, coordinating meetings, and managing communications. Facilitated the organization of events, and workshops, fostering an environment conducive to creativity and entrepreneurship within the GFX/VFX domain.
